&gt; Try using the junit task and under it there is a batchtest element.
&gt; 
&gt; &lt;batchtest fork=&quot;yes&quot; todir=&quot;${build.test}&quot; failureProperty=&quot;failed&quot;&gt;
&gt;     &lt;fileset dir=&quot;${build.src}&quot;&gt;
&gt;        &lt;include name=&quot;**/test/**/*Test.java&quot; /&gt;
&gt;        &lt;exclude name=&quot;com/lse/test/util/*Test.java&quot; /&gt;
&gt;     &lt;/fileset&gt;
&gt; &lt;/batchtest&gt;

if you don&#39;t want to use this solution, JUnit-addons provides the
DirectorySuiteBuilder and ArchiveSuiteBuilder (for jar/zip files) classes.

